# [IVY](../wg/ivy.html)

## Summary

The IVY (Network Inventory) Working Group met at IETF 126. The session covered status updates on the core models, progressed discussions on active working group documents including software, location, and entitlement extensions, and reviewed the open issues for passive network inventory. Additionally, the group received a report on the IVY hackathon results showing successful interoperability testing and discussed a new proposal on Cryptographic Asset Discovery and Inventory (CADI).

---

## Key Discussion Points

### 1. Working Group Status Update
The chairs, Aihua Guo and Daniele Ceccarelli, opened the meeting with the [00-admin slides](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-ivy-00-admin-slides-00). 
* **Core Model:** Sent back to authors for final edits. Expected to be ready for the IESG in a few weeks.
* **Network Inventory Topology (`draft-ietf-ivy-network-inventory-topology`):** Passed Working Group Last Call (WGLC). Olga Havel is shepherding the document. The write-up is held until final comments are addressed in the next release.
